com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.mrcm.core.widget.bean

Class WidgetBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.b2international.commons.beans.BeanPropertyChangeSupporter
      • com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.mrcm.core.widget.bean.WidgetBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ModeledWidgetBean

    public abstract class WidgetBean
extends BeanPropertyChangeSupporter
implements Serializable
    An abstract backing bean for a UI element that displays a property of a SNOMED CT concept; carries the minimum amount of information necessary for presentation and conversion to/from the corresponding EMF model element.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • onCloneAction

        public WidgetBean onCloneAction()
        Callback method invoked when the user invokes the "clone" action, usually resulting in a cloned instance (based on the same widget model as this instance, if such a model exists) being added to the backing model.

        The default implementation throws UnsupportedOperationException; subclasses should override.

      • onRetireAction

        public void onRetireAction()
        Callback method invoked when the user invokes the "retire" action, which removes this element from the backing model.

        The default implementation throws UnsupportedOperationException; subclasses should override.

      • isCloneActionEnabled

        public boolean isCloneActionEnabled()
        Checks if the "clone" action should be enabled, allowing the user to add more instances of this bean.
        Returns:
        true if the "clone" action should be enabled in the context menu beside the element, false otherwise
